[recv] {"method":"item/completed","params":{"item":{"type":"agentMessage","id":"msg_0942eea3560fea8d0169c54e7413a48191b931ba85b710781b","text":"Created the board in [index.circuit.tsx](/workspace/index.circuit.tsx). It’s a minimal RP2040 breakout with:\n\n- RP2040, external QSPI flash, 12 MHz crystal, 3.3 V LDO, USB-C, status LED\n- dual 20-pin breakout headers plus a 3-pin SWD header\n- JLCPCB-imported silicon/connector parts from `imports/`, with JLC part numbers pinned for the passive BOM\n- no tscircuit registry components and no `routingDisabled`\n\nValidation: `npm run typecheck` passes, and `tsci check netlist index.circuit.tsx` reports 0 errors / 0 warnings. A previous `tsci build index.circuit.tsx` completed and wrote [dist/index/circuit.json](/workspace/dist/index/circuit.json), but the autorouter is unstable on this dense 2-layer board and can sometimes hang or emit iteration warnings during rebuilds. If you want, I can do a second pass to ease routing by changing the header mapping or adding routing hints/manual traces.","phase":"final_answer","memoryCitation":null},"threadId":"019d2aaf-1cc7-73d0-9c45-616dc01c5a32","turnId":"019d2aaf-1ccc-7cf2-9773-3b18dd455489"}}
